Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on controllers in robotics, specifically bipedal locomotion on the ATRIAS robot. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses using data-efficient learning techniques, such as Bayesian Optimization, to optimize controllers. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with designing controllers for a physical system. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible categories as the paper discusses using simulation and optimization techniques to learn controllers.
